			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>danille wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Just a clarification on the 100% snare thing. Please correct me if I am wrong on this.
<br />

<br />
The way I understand it is:
<br />

<br />
<snip>
<br />

<br />
2) 100% snare loses the proximity aggro that our current root has. so nearby mobs would not be aggroed by the snare..correct?..</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Not exactly... 100% snare would mean that proximity is no longer the governing factor for who is getting hit.  The PC with the most aggro would continue to be the focus of the mob's attacks.
<br />

<br />
Currently, using an earth pet in a group/raid, when the root lands, the closest PC with any aggro at all gets beat on, regardless of who has the most aggro.  With 100% snare, the tank using his nifty taunting and aggro-generating abilities would retain aggro, even if the rogue behind the mob is a bit closer - just like if there was no snare/root at all.  A healer or nuker could still be summoned, but if aggro shifted the mob would not run around forcing melees to chase it.
<br />

<br />
The other difference would be upon reaching the "flee" health level.  At that point the mob would turn to run and just stand there while it gets finished off.  This happens already with most snares, as the flee speed is lower than the regular speed of the mob.  With root, the mob continues to fight until dead, knowing it cannot get away.
<br />

<br />
To be honest, I'm fine with earth pet keeping root, <span style="font-weight: bold">IF they re-code rooted mob behaviour.</span>  If the mob would still attack based on it's hate list of PCs in melee range, then the rest is fine.  IMO.  I think other things can be done to fix up our pet situation.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fazzadien Elementweaver</a> 
<br />
