Looked on lucy, I see no stun component on our dots.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
You're right about that one.  I thought they had a stun on them?  Guess not.  I dunno where I got that idea from.  =P
<br />

<br />
But as for the exploit, I would say doing pretty much anything that wasn't intended with something they gave us would be classified as an exploit.  They didn't envision kiting when they put snare in, but that's what happened.  They also didn't envision FD pulling when FD was put in the game, but that's also the result.
<br />

<br />
For kiting, they seem to be OK with it now.  But 100% snare isn't kiting.  You don't need to move at all.  You just need to sit there, your pet takes no damage, you take no damage, and after an initial nukefest, with pet taunt off, do you really think you have to nuke that much to keep agro?  I guess somebody could test it with normal kiting (get a dru/rng to snare it for you), and see how much you really have to nuke to keep agro.  But unless it is an EXTREME amount of mana, I don't see it as a barrier.  Even if it was, with 100% snare, you are NEVER in danger.  Your pet possibly, but never you.  Root can break anytime, but snare can't.  If your pet bites it, you almost certainly have the time to gate.  Even less risk than kiters have, since even with them snare is resisted.  With us, it would be "send pet in, and make sure it is snared".  The dru/wiz/rng needs to worry if they get resists, and get rocked by the mob they are trying to kite.  With us, we would almost certainly have enough time from the pet to make SURE one of the pet snares worked.
<br />

<br />
And Fazzadien, I think your idea is the best one here.  Just change root from proximity agro to actually attacking whoever is on its hate list that is in range, and not just the closest.  Was this the way it used to be?  Or was it always like it is now?  Or what?  I know they changed pet vs PC agro (pets used to be able to tank even when PCs were in range), but what about this situation?  I would say that would be the simplest change, though perhaps it isn't, and requires a LARGE code change.<br />_________________<br />Eriol Telcontar
